article.headline: East Tenn. St. 84, UT-Chattanooga 72
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. (AP) -- Tim Smith scored 27 points to lead East Tennessee State to an 84-72 victory Tuesday night over Chattanooga, the 16th straight victory for the Buccaneers. ETSU (24-4, 15-0) shot 54 percent from the field, including 9-of-10 by Ben Rhoda, who had 19 points. Jerald Fields had 20 points and Zakee Wadood 10 points and 10 rebounds for the Bucs, who led 28-24 at halftime. Ray Trowell had 15 points to lead Chattanooga (16-10, 9-6). Mindaugas Katelynas scored 14 points and grabbed 13 rebounds for the Mocs, while Alphonso Pugh had 14 points and Jason Rogan 12. Chattanooga shot nearly 50 percent from 3-point range (10-of-21), but only 41.6 percent from the rest of the court. The game was tight throughout the first half, with ETSU leading by four points twice, including halftime. The Mocs never led in the game. ETSU took charge in the final 20 minutes, building its lead to 10 points at 47-37 with 12:50 left on a layup by Rhoda. The Bucs continued to pour it on, shooting nearly 65 percent in the second half and building their lead to as much as 70-50 with 5:08 to play on a 3-pointer by Smith.
